HEADWORD: Interocular
<hw>In`ter*oc"u*lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Between, or
within, the eyes; <as>as, the <ex>interocular</ex> distance</as>;
situated between the eyes, as the antenn⟦ae⟧ of some insects.</def>⟦br⟧
